2:33 PM; Case called for Plea/sentencing hearing. Prosecuting attorney Charles Patrick Hoffmann in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Daniel A Massey in court.  Attorney Daniel R Skarie in court for Daniel A Massey.  Court notes the State has filed an Amended Information adding Count 2.  Atty. Skarie acknowledges receipt, waives reading, and enters initial not guilty plea to Count 2 of the Amended Information.  Court also notes a plea questionnaire has been filed and recites the offer as listed in the questionnaire.  State confirms and outlines some additional parts of the offer.  Atty. Skarie confirms the offer.  Court conducts plea colloquy with the defendant.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1, Court finds defendant guilty of Count 1.  Court orders Count 2 dismissed by operation of law.  Court also orders case 22TR3273 dismissed in its entirety pursuant to the offer.

Sentencing arguments made by the State.
Sentencing arguments made by Atty. Skarie.
Defendant presents statements.

COUNT 1:
The Court Orders the Following:

Withheld sentence (Court will award 2 Days Credit IF defendant is revoked and sentenced)

Term of Probation: 2 Years

Conditions of Probation:
-	Follow any conditions deemed appropriate by Agent;
-	AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
-	Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.'s;
-	No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
-	No use or possession of any controlled substances without a valid doctor's prescription
-	No operation of a motor vehicle without a valid driver's license;
-	Attendance at a Victim Impact Panel;
-	Comply with all rules of OWI Treatment Court and remain in good standing.

Condition Time: 300 Days Total:
First 60 Days Huber with NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS OR on Electronic Monitoring at the discretion of the OWI Treatment team - To commence  forthwith;
Balance - STAYED.  To be used at the agents discretion. To be served Straight-Time if imposed.


DL REVOCATION:  36 months.
IGNITITION INTERLOCK: 36 months.

FINE:  $1,758.00 (includes IID surcharge);

DNA Surcharge: $250.00;

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35.00 to be paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forwarded to City of Waukesha Police Department.

Total costs/fine/forfeiture:  Court to apply the $3000.00 Cash Bail on deposit; any remaining bond to be refunded to the poster. Failure to pay;  will result in a civil judgment.

Felony warnings, immigration warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
